%S A319879 1,8,13,18,21,26,29,34,37,40,45,48,51,56,59,62,65,70,73,76,79,84,87,
%T A319879 90,93,96,101,104,107,110,113,118,121,124,127,130,133,138,141,144,147,
%U A319879 150,153,158,161,164,167,170,173,176,181,184,187,190,193,196,199,204
%N A319879 a(n) = minimal number m of unit squares needed to make a figure formed from squares (joined edge to edge) which has n holes.
%C A319879 The holes must not touch each other.
%C A319879 A valid figure needs at least one square.
%D A319879 Jean-Paul Delahaye, Des trous à entourer avec parcimonie, Pour la Science, No. 501, Juillet 2019, pp. 82-87.
%H A319879 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A319879/b319879.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%F A319879 For n >= 1, a(n) = 3*(n+1) + 2*floor(sqrt(4*n-3)). - _Zhuorui He_, Jun 29 2026
%e A319879 Examples from _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jan 30 2019 for n = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4:
